 "body": "<p>S58, S59 Income Tax (Trading and Other Income) Act 2005</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"income-tax\">Income Tax</h2>\n\n<p>A statutory deduction in computing the profits of a trade applies to the incidental costs of raising loan finance which would otherwise not be an allowable deduction. The rules apply only to Income Tax.</p>\n\n<p>There are special rules regarding the incidental costs of raising loan finance for businesses using the cash basis - see <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/business-income-manual/bim70040\">BIM70040</a></p>\n\n<h2 id=\"corporation-tax\">Corporation Tax</h2>\n\n<p>For Corporation Tax, incidental costs of raising loan finance are dealt with under the loan relationships rules. For details see <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/corporate-finance-manual/cfm30000\">CFM30000</a> onwards.</p>\n\n<p>The guidance covers the following:</p>\n",
